        <h2>Why is SyncTime Better for Ticketing?</h2>

        <h3>1. Direct Measurement</h3>
        <p>
            SyncTime measures the <strong>target server's HTTP time</strong> directly instead of standard time (NTP).
            You can directly check "what time Ticketmaster's server thinks it is."
        </p>

        <h3>2. Real-time Check</h3>
        <p>
            NTP syncs only once a week, but SyncTime <strong>measures fresh every time</strong>.
            You can check the latest server time 5 minutes before ticketing.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Network Latency Compensation</h3>
        <p>
            SyncTime doesn't just read the Date header—it
            <strong>calculates RTT (Round Trip Time) to compensate for network latency</strong>.
            This implements the same principle as NTP at the HTTP level.
        </p>

        <div class="method-comparison"
            style="background-color: #e8f5e9; padding: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid #4caf50; margin: 1rem 0;">
