        <h2>Precautions and Limitations</h2>

        <h3>HTTP Date Limitations</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> Lower accuracy than NTP (network variation)</li>
            <li><strong>Server load:</strong> Response time increases during server overload before opening</li>
            <li><strong>Caching:</strong> CDN or proxy servers may cache Date headers</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>NTP Limitations</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Server independence:</strong> Can't know target server's actual time</li>
            <li><strong>Sync frequency:</strong> Only auto-syncs once a week</li>
            <li><strong>Firewall:</strong> Some networks block NTP port (123)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>For ticketing success, use both</strong>:
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>NTP:</strong> Sync your computer to standard time beforehand for baseline accuracy</li>
            <li><strong>SyncTime:</strong> Identify target server's exact time right before ticketing</li>
        </ol>
